        "timestamp": "2022-12-22 16:31:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nFor a property of type list of complex types - adding a tosca function to one of the sub properties works fine, but when trying to set a tosca function value to a second sub property of the same property results in an error saying the value for the first sub property is invalid.\nSeen of Lists of complex types, maps of complex types and just complex types.\n\nAlso when this error occurs the TOSCA Function button is disabled when any of the sub properties is selected\n\nAlso when adding a get_property tosca function to a sub property of a complex type in a map - if no property of the correct type exists an error is shown (which is correct) but the type mentioned in the error is the complex type rather than the type of the sub property being set",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
